name: Rock Wave
description: An arch of sandstone catches light from far above and stands out from the surrounding darkness deep inside Buckskin Gulch in southern Utah.

name: Bighorn Portrait
description: A Desert Bighorn Sheep soaks up the warm rays of the rising sun on a cold morning in southern Utah.

name: Sandstone Form
description: Sandstone takes on a strangely human form in the Coyote Buttes Wilderness of southern Utah.

name: Bighorn Kaleidoscope
description: A Male Bighorn Sheep framed through the out-of-focus sunlit branches of a Juniper tree in southern Utah.

name: Cottonwood Form
description: The beautiful curves of a backlit Cottonwood tree in Zion National Park in southern Utah.

name: Velvet Stone
description: The texture of sandstone deep inside Buckskin Gulch in southern Utah, the world's longest slot canyon.

name: Emanating
description: A thirty second exposure at midday blurs fast-moving clouds over a lone Ponderosa Pine in the backcountry of Zion National Park.

name: Virgin River Sunset
description: Colorful clouds over the Virgin River at sunset in Zion National Park.

name: Zion Winter Storm
description: A small cloud hangs over imposing Sandstone Cliffs after a snowstorm in Zion National Park.

name: Last Light
description: The last moments of light from the setting sun illuminate a sandstone cliff face near Zion National Park in southern Utah.

name: Catching Fire
description: A leaf catches the light of the setting sun in a dark forest in western Oregon.

name: Life Finds a Way
description: Small desert plants grow from a thin crack in sandstone in the Coyote Buttes Wilderness of southern Utah.

name: Tree Silhouette
description: A small dead Juniper is silhouetted against a massive sandstone mountain in Zion National Park.

name: Shimmering Cottonwoods
description: A stand of bare, sun-lit Cottonwood trees against a dark canyon wall in Zion National Park.

name: Stone Rainbow
description: Multi-colored sandstone seems to flow like water in the Coyote Buttes wilderness.

name: Warm and Cool
description: Snow-covered Ponderosa Pines against sandstone cliffs in Zion National Park.

name: Zion Reflection
description: One of the massive sandstone peaks in Zion National Park is reflected in the waters of the Virgin River.

name: Crescent Venus
description: The crescent moon and Venus seem to balance each other in the last light of the setting sun.

name: Sandstone Band
description: A sandstone wall is the only thing not snow-covered after a severe winter storm near Zion National park in southern Utah.

name: Whitetail Pastel
description: A White Tail buck framed through foliage in southern Utah.

name: Hanging in Space
description: The moon sets over isolated Fir trees on a hilltop overlooking the Clearwater River in northern Idaho.

name: Bighorn Silhouette
description: A Bighorn Sheep backlit by the rising sun in southern Utah.

name: Texture and Form
description: A young Dragonfly awaits the drying rays of the sun in a field in western Oregon.

name: Pastel Forest
description: By moving the camera from side to side towards the end of a 20-second exposure, I was able to impart a more painterly feel to this scene in northern Idaho.

name: Rising
description: As the sun breaks through storm clouds and hits the forest above the Clearwater River in northern Idaho, steam rises quickly from into the sky from the wet trees.

name: Trillium with Ferns
description: A chaotic tangle of out-of-focus sword ferns lends an almost aquatic feel to this portrait of a Trillium flower in a forest in western Oregon.

name: Ocean's Halo
description: Sunlight reflecting off high-altitude ice crystals creates a bright solar halo over a shallow river on the central Oregon coast.

name: Thor's Well
description: Water recedes back into Thor's Well, a huge sinkhole on a rocky shelf at Cape Perpetua on the central Oregon coast.

name: Bed of Mussels
description: Three sea lions relax on a rocky island off the central Oregon coast.

name: Fading Light
description: A sandy beach reflects puffy clouds at dusk on the central Oregon coast.

name: Waiting
description: A lone Canada goose stands in the ocean surf at sunrise on the central Oregon coast.

name: Spring Vibrance
description: A sea of Western Skunk Cabbage brightens the forest floor on the central Oregon coast.

name: Path to the Sea
description: Sunset light over a washboard stream on the southern Oregon coast.

name: In the Shadow of Giants
description: A small tree grows between giants in Redwood National Park.

name: Clinging to Life
description: A solar halo surrounds a tree-topped island on the southern Oregon coast.

name: Cape Blanco Sunrise
description: Cape Blanco State Park under beautiful sunrise light.

name: High Noon
description: The midday sun hangs over a massive rock pillar on the southern Oregon coast.

name: Corona Arch
description: A juniper tree framed against the massive Corona Arch near Arches National Park.

name: Sandstone Skylight
description: Shadows and light form interesting shapes around this rock feature near Moab, Utah.

name: Cold Stone
description: A wave washes over a smooth basalt stone in late evening on the southern Oregon coast.

name: Driftwood Lines
description: A huge sea stack looms over a field of driftwood on the southern Oregon coast.

name: Emerging
description: A clump of small mushrooms sprouts from a downed Ponderosa pine in central Oregon.

name: Sea Grass Curves
description: Wave tossed sea grass forms beautiful curves on the southern Oregon coast.

name: Desert Solitude
description: A lone, long-dead Cottonwood tree under the full moon in White Sands National Park.  On many of the nights I spent in the park I camped near this tree, because I think in a strange way it provided a sense of companionship in the seemingly endless and largely lifeless dunes.

name: Sharp Shadows
description: The evening sun casts a Yucca's shadow across the sand in White Sands National Park.

name: Yosemite Cliff Face
description: Light breaks through stormy skies and illuminates a cliff face in Yosemite National Park.

name: Winter Blush
description: The first dusting of snow along a creek in Western Oregon.

name: Teasel Tendrils
description: The tendrils of a Teasel flower head form beautiful curves in winter in western Oregon.

name: Desert Gathering
description: A cluster of Ladybugs on the center of a Blue Agave plant in Central Arizona.  I was in the middle of a 300 mile hike through central Arizona in the dead of winter when I came upon this, so it was definitely a surprise.

name: Wild Apache Plume
description: An Apache Plume seedhead silhouetted against the setting sun in northern New Mexico.  Before I had a digital camera and Live View, shots like this required me to stare at the sun through the viewfinder for long periods of time.  Glad those days are over.

name: Sea Stack Panoramic
description: A river flows into the sea below a field of sea stacks near Bandon, Oregon.

name: Sea Foam Streaks
description: Rivulets of sea foam course back to the sea in the wake of a large wave in Ecola State Park on the Oregon Coast.

name: Mantis Lines
description: A Praying Mantis hangs from grass early one morning in a field in western Oregon.

name: Light Rain
description: Light rain falls on a small plant and its reflection in a flooded forest in western Oregon

name: Near and Far
description: A solar halo surrounds a tree clinging to life on a sea stack off the central Oregon coast.

name: Gull Reflection
description: A seagull and its reflection in a tidal pool on the central Oregon coast.  The golden color of the water is from a sandstone wall behind the pool, lit by the midday sun.

name: Anger and Fear
description: An angry Kelp Crab warns me to keep my distance.  It was only when I got very close that it would raise its claws like this, so I'd get close and then jump back and try to get a shot with my camera flat on the sand before it lowered its claws.

name: Ocean Turmoil
description: A long exposure blurs tossing waves under dark skies on the central Oregon coast.

name: Starfish Reflection
description: A bright orange starfish seems to lounge against basalt rock on the Oregon coast.  To get a full reflection, I had my tripod-mounted camera just an inch or two above the surface of the water.  This image placed in the 2013 Windland Smith Rice International Competition, in the Animal Antics category.

name: Golden Wings
description: A dragonfly's wings stand out amidst the mute colors of a pre-dawn morning.

name: Journey's End
description: A Silver Salmon's long journey from the ocean comes to an end up Oregon's Eagle Creek.

name: Water, Light, and Stone
description: A wisp of a cloud drifts over rock walls lit by the setting sun in the Grand Canyon.

name: Fungal Forest
description: An underside view of a group of Oyster Mushrooms sprouting from a decaying tree trunk in western Oregon.  To even the exposure between the base of the mushrooms and the outer edges, I held my coat flush to the tree over them and created a little darkroom, and the shutter speed went up to about 10 seconds.

name: Rose Hip Dancer
description: Raindrops hang from scarlet rose hips in a field in western Oregon.

name: Living Candle
description: A blurred leaf completes this interesting composition of an apple branch in late fall.  The young shoots were sprouting around the base of an ancient apple tree that was part of a long-abandoned orchard on National Forest land.

name: Eastern Oregon Prairie
description: Black cows graze under stormy skies in eastern Oregon.  The wind was gusting to 60 mph and I could barely keep myself upright, but the cows didn't even seem to notice it.

name: Walled In
description: A cane toad looks up from between the buttress roots of a rainforest tree in western Ecuador.

name: Seal Rocks Torrent
description: Water rushes through a channel toward the Seal Rocks formation on the Oregon coast.  The main challenge in taking this photo was keeping myself and my tripod steady in the powerful current.

name: Colorado River Moonset
description: A crescent moon sets over the tranquil waters of the Colorado River.  What I remember most clearly from the 3 weeks I spent rafting the Grand Canyon were the perilous, frothing rapids, but really the river looked like this most of the time, quiet and peaceful.

name: Leaves and Light
description: An image that for me conveys the feeling of fall in Oregon. Turning leaves, muted light, and soft rain.

name: Toad Reflection
description: A toad leaps from a rock in a rare rain puddle on the northwestern side of Kauaii.  The island is only 30 miles across yet is home to the wettest spot on Earth, a tropical rainforest, and an arid desert.

name: Liquid Light
description: Sandstone and sky reflected in a tiny waterfall in Havasu Canyon.  The waters of the Havasu River flow from a spring and contain travertine, a mineral that over time has built many of these small waterfalls in the river channel.

name: Smokey Forest
description: Smoke from a nearby wildfire drifts through a recently burned Ponderosa Pine forest near Prescott, Arizona.

name: Curves
description: A simple composition of a dune, a shadow, and the sky.  Scenes  like this are common in White Sands, but can still be difficult to capture.

name: Receding Wave
description: A massive wave recedes after slamming into a sandstone wall on the Oregon coast.  It was exhilarating standing on a small lip of rock and being buffeted by strong winds above the churning water, but I didn't stick around long! This image was Highly Commended in the 2013 Memorial Maria Luisa Competition.

name: Patagonia Rainbow
description: The most bright and vivid double rainbow i've ever seen arches over Mesquite trees in southern Arizona.  I was watching the sunset under light rain when it occurred to me to turn around, that the center of a rainbow is exactly opposite the sun in the sky, and after a few stunned moments I set about taking this photo.

name: Queen Anne's Lines
description: A stark portrait of Queen Anne's Lace in a field in western Oregon.  Tall grass in the background conveys a sense of movement to the image.

name: Moonlit Cottonwood
description: A lone, long-dead Cottonwood Tree under star trails in White Sands National Monument, illuminated by a setting crescent moon.  I've never felt as lonely as I did on winter nights far back in those dunes, and in that vast expanse of sand even a tree can impart a sense of companionship.

name: Vine Snake Strike
description: A Vine Snake opens its mouth to strike in the jungles of western Ecuador.  I was working in a banana plantation when I found this snake, and discovered in the course of shooting it that if I got just the right distance away it would hold its mouth open and wait, and would strike only if I moved too close.  Unfortunately the right distance was pretty narrow, and I was bitten more than once before it was over.  This image won 2nd Place in the Color section of the Best of College Photography Competition in 2004.

name: The Hunt
description: The moment before a Crab Spider made a grab for a fly.  It didn't catch it.

name: Heliconia Silhouette
description: A heliconia butterfly in a spot of light at dusk in southern Costa Rica.

name: Tuckup Canyon
description: A small creek winds through Tuckup Canyon in a remote part of Grand Canyon National Park.

name: Shimmering
description: A golden Cottonwood Tree in Havasu Canyon in the fall.

name: Blurred Leaves
description: Fall leaves are blurred during a long exposure of a stream in Oregon's Cascade Mountains.

name: Teasel Portrait
description: A stark portrait of a dried Teasel flowerhead in a forest in western Oregon.

name: Cottonwood Silhouette
description: A huge Cottonwood silhouetted against a clear sky in northern New Mexico.

name: Wild Tendrils
description: The interesting shapes made by a tendril silhouetted against the sky in the Peruvian Amazon.

name: Swan Flowers
description: A simple composition of two tiny flowers in central Texas.

name: Forest Floor
description: A frog watches from the edge of a water-filled leaf on the forest floor in Tambopata National Preserve, Peru.  To get an interesting perspective, I laid flat on the ground so the lens was actually angled slightly upwards.

name: Covered Sunflower
description: A bee is thwarted in it's quest for nectar by two petals covering  a sunflower in central Texas.  I often see individual petals of flowers pulled in over their centers, and it's almost always the work of a spider making a home.

name: Wintry Burn
description: Wet snow sticks to the trunks of evergreen trees killed in a wildfire on the Deschutes National Forest in central Oregon.

name: Dying Sunflower
description: A wilted sunflower is highlighted by the brilliant yellow of one in full bloom.

name: Sun and Rain
description: The sun illuminates the forest  behind a raindrop hanging on the edge of an oak leaf in central Texas.

name: Dragonfly Pastel
description: A Green Darner dragonfly in tall grass.

name: Laying in Wait
description: An Orb Weaver waits from prey on it's dew-covered web in a field in western Oregon.

name: Wintry Blue
description: A heliconia butterfly in a spot of light at dusk in southern Costa Rica.

name: Water's Edge
description: A small crab's reflection in a tidal stream in Corcovado National Park.  To get a low enough angle, I was kneeling in the stream with my mounted camera just a couple of inches above the water surface.

name: Spot of Yellow
description: A lone yellow flower grows from lush grass in central Texas.

name: Winter Blur
description: By zooming in halfway through a 10 second exposure, I was able to get this interesting shot of a forest after a heavy snowfall.

name: Jagged Sky
description: Wispy clouds drift over gnarled trees on an island off the southern Oregon coast.

name: Snake Silhouette
description: A Rough Green Snake is silhouetted against the sun as it moves between branches in Pedernales State Park.  This image is on the cover of the UK edition of The Lower River, by Paul Theroux.

name: Sands of Time
description: Dried grass blown by the wind etches a circle in white sand.  I saw this phenomenon often in White Sands and wanted to capture it, but couldn't find a suitable example until this one.

name: Ponderosa Field
description: A dense Ponderosa Pine forest in the Mount Jefferson Wilderness after a brief winter snowfall.

name: A Break in the Clouds
description: The evening sun emerges briefly between a low cloudbank and the horizon off the Washington coast.

name: Tropical Fall
description: Colorful leaves trapped against the stream bed by rushing water.  There's no Fall in Costa Rica, just wet and dry seasons, but fI often saw fall colors in individual trees scattered throughout the diverse forest.

name: Mantis on Agave
description: A Praying Mantis on the youngest leaf of a Blue Agave in Big Bend National Park.

name: Shades of White
description: A white crab spider on a white english daisy against a white sky.

name: Crescents
description: A circling buzzard mirrors a crescent moon in Enchanted Rock State Park.  These birds are always there at a certain spot on one of the high granite domes, so I laid on my back and was eventually able to capture one as it streaked by the moon.

name: Lost in Snow
description: A tiny mosquito lost in a sea of snow.  After an unusually dry October in western Oregon we suddenly got 6 inches of snow overnight, so I decided to head up into the mountains to photograph some waterfalls.  As often happens, my attention was drawn to something on a much different scale.

name: Arched Grass
description: A Praying Mantis hangs from a grass arch in a field in western Oregon.

name: Crater Lake Winter Portrait
description: A panoramic view of Crater Lake in the dead of winter.  I've never suffered as much in the course of taking a photo as I did for this one.  Two days trapped in a tent, brutal treks out and back, near zero degree temperatures, and not enough food, but it was absolutely worth it.  This image was Commended in the Panoramic category of the 2013 Sony World Photography Open.

name: Skyfalls
description: A view from behind a massive waterfall up Eagle Creek in Oregon's Columbia River Gorge.

name: Morpho
description: A dead Blue Morpho butterfly in leaf little in Corcovado National Park.  I used a wide-angle lens positioned almost on top of the butterfly and a 2 minute exposure to get this shot.  About a minute in, I began slowly zooming in and out to add a feeling of movement to the photo.  The Blue Morpho, rivaled only by the Scarab beetle, is one of the world's most reflective animals, meaning that its body reflects a higher percentage of light than that of any other animal on Earth.

name: Sinuous Grass
description: Dried grass frames a dark spot in the snow in the Gila Wilderness.  Photos like this that are composed of so little are often the ones I'm most proud of.  I think it takes much more skill to make a beautiful photo with just a blade of grass or a shadow than with an eagle or a sunset.

name: Cycle of Life
description: A dried pod in central Texas cracked slightly open to reveal the seed inside.

name: Hovering Orb Weaver
description: An Orb Weaver spider seems to hover in space against a cold background in western Oregon.

name: Seeds in the Sky
description: Apache Plume seed heads against the sky in northern New Mexico.

name: Bright Heliconia
description: Heliconias were the most common butterflies I saw in Corcovado National Park, but rarely held still long enough to be photographed.  This one was preparing to roost for the night.

name: White Dragon
description: A dragonfly on a grass head in western Oregon, shot against the bright morning sky.

name: Currents Made Visible
description: The gentle currents of a stream in the Cascade Mountains are made visible by the fall leaves they carry in circles.

name: Soft Dragonfly
description: A dragonfly clings to a grass head in front of a soft background.

name: Kapok Hopper
description: A tiny Hopper perches on the large thorns of a Kapok Tree in the Peruvian Amazon.  This image was taken at my macro lens's maximum magnification, so the vertical distance is just 1 inch.

name: Coming Home
description: A mother hummingbird returns to her nest just as a thunderhead darkens the forest.  Moments later powerful winds hit the tree canopy and heavy, hard fruit started hitting the ground with enough force to leave little craters.  After getting photographs of her landing in her nest, I took off running and didn't stop till I was out of the forest.  I don't plan on being killed by falling fruit.

name: Havasu Sunset
description: The Setting sun illuminates clouds and a row of cliffs at the entrance to Havasu Canyon.  The hike out of the canyon is long and slow but not very tough until the last mile or two, when it suddenly gets very steep and feels never ending.  It was difficult, but for a view like this I would gladly struggle any day.

name: Joshua Tree Polaris
description: A Joshua Tree seems to emanate a radio signal on a cold winter night.  I don't know what caused the strange color on the horizon, though it could have been the faint glow of a faraway town.

name: Moon and Planets
description: A serene moment when the moon, Venus, and Jupiter seem to be balancing each other in space over a fading sunset in White Sands National Monument.

name: Trillium Portrait
description: A simple portrait of a Trillium flower in a forest in western Oregon.

name: Hidden World
description: A spider hangs from its web attached to the gills of a large mushroom in western Oregon.  Leaves of a small plant partially block the subject from the lens.

name: Vibrating Skimmer
description: A tiny skimmer vibrates on the water surface and sends out ripples in a creek in Corcovado National Park.

name: Why?
description: Low, fast moving clouds illuminated by a half moon drift over Diamond Peak in the Oregon cascades, their movement blurred slightly by a 30 second exposure.

name: Delicate
description: A fragment of a dew-covered spiderweb in a field in western Oregon.

name: Sweep of Dune
description: The rising sun illuminates the curve of a dune in White Sands National Monument.

name: Moth and Grass
description: A moth seems to hang in space next to a single blade of grass.  After trying almost every conceivable angle, I laid down beneath the moth and framed it against the bright sky.  The slight blur on its right side is the seed head its holding onto.

name: Dragon Glow
description: A dragonfly basks in the first warm rays of sunlight after a cold Oregon night.  I used my hand to shield the lens from the light and prevent flare.

name: Waves of Sand
description: The texture of a dune and distant mountains in White Sands National Monument.

name: Settling Down
description: One butterfly settled down for the night, and another flitting around in search of the perfect spot.  I was shooting film at the time, so I didn't know for over a month if I had gotten what I was after.

name: Droplet Over Flower
description: A tiny droplet of morning dew hangs over a flower in northern Arizona.  The year before this area had been burned by a huge wildfire, and the rich green grass and colorful flowers were a stark contrast to the blackened tree trunks surrounding them.

name: Icefall
description: A small waterfall up Oregon's Eagle Creek encased in ice after three days and nights below freezing.

name: Saguaro Ocean View
description: The sun rises over a field of Saguaro on the Mexican coast.

name: Soft Snow
description: A swollen river flows under snow-laden branches in the Cascade Foothills.

name: Angled Snow Flowers
description: I ventured up into the Gearhart Mountains of Oregon one winter, and was stopped by snow about 10 miles from the trailhead I was heading for.  Before heading back towards lower ground I explored the area a little bit, and eventually found these tiny dried flowers sticking out of the snow.

name: Ribbon Falls
description: A thin ribbon of water cascades down a smooth rock face into a pool below in western Oregon.  A few days later the first October rains came and this gentle stream became a raging torrent.

name: Vibrant Sea Foam
description: Brilliantly colored sea foam bubbles in a tidal pool reflect the photographer in Cape Perpetua on the Oregon coast.  I'm not sure what caused the bubbles to be colored, whether it was the refraction of sunlight or a natural oil seep or something else, but it sure is beautiful.  The reflection is me in my raingear straddling the tidal pool, and the three straight legs of my tripod.  This image was the winner of the People in Nature category of the 2012 Windland Smith Rice International, and is currently on display in the Smithsonian Natural History Museum in Washington, D.C.

name: Ready to Strike
description: A Western Diamondback rattlesnake zeroes in on a very nervous photographer.

name: Tree Island
description: A solar halo surrounds sea stacks and a tenacious tree on the central Oregon coast.

name: Rattler Tongue
description: A Western Diamondback rattlesnake tastes the air on a chilly morning in central Arizona.  Rattlesnakes are much easier to work with in cooler weather because it slows them down and they're much less aggressive.

name: Moon Streak
description: A streak of light cuts through the full moon over the Seal Rocks formation on the Oregon coast.  It wasn't until my camera lens fogged up and I wiped it off that this streak appeared, and after a few shots it disappeared.

name: Proxy Falls
description: An ultra-wide angle lens distorts a small riffle into appearing as big as Proxy Falls, one of the most spectacular waterfalls in Oregon.

name: Glowing Web
description: A dewy spiderweb catches the first rays of sunlight in a field in western Oregon.  From the first moment the sun crests the horizon it is often bright enough to cause lens flare, and to prevent that you can simply use your hand to block it from hitting the lens.

name: Saguaro With Stars
description: A tall Saguaro cactus under star trails in southern Arizona.

name: Sycamore
description: A Sycamore leaf floats in still water in Barton Creek near Austin, TX.

name: Wood Lizard Warning
description: An Amazon Wood Lizard warns me to keep my distance in the Peruvian Amazon.  I only spotted this well-camouflaged little guy because it was right next to the shoe that I bent down to tie.  It makes me wonder how much I missed in my time there.

name: Tendrils and Sun
description: Two tendrils from a Teasel flowerhead form a beautiful shape beneath the evening sun in western Oregon.

name: Pastel Sun
description: The sun filters through dried flower stalks in White Sands National Monument.

name: Owl Butterfly Portrait
description: An Owl Butterfly rests on a dried banana leaf in western Ecuador.  Looking at this photo, it's not hard to guess how these beautiful butterflies got their name.

name: Mushroom Home
description: A tiny fly is dwarfed by tiny mushrooms on the forest floor in Oregon's Umpqua National Forest.

name: Mushroom With Frond
description: A tiny, inch tall mushroom sprouts from a rotting twig in the center of a large fern in the Peruvian Amazon.  The fern was growing from a tree about 8 feet off the ground, so I had to hold the camera over my head and compose with Live View to get the shot.

name: Moth on Fern
description: A simple portrait of a moth on a fern in the Ecuadorian Andes.

name: Big Bend Moonset
description: A crescent moon hangs over rolling hills and the last glow of sunset in Big Bend National Park.  The clear desert air in such places can result in morning and evening light that is difficult to match.

name: Mushroom Bokeh
description: Two tiny mushrooms sprout from a mossy log in Umpqua National Forest.  When the fall rains come to Oregon they bring dormant mushrooms to life, and it seems that every wet log and patch of ground is host to them.

name: Moon Falls
description: After falling 150 feet over Moon Falls, this stream winds through a stand of ancient spruce and fir trees.

name: Spider Silhouette
description: Golden light filtering through the forest frames a spider in Corcovado National Park.

name: Yellow
description: A brightly colored maple leaf on black volcanic rock in a stream below Oregon's Moon Falls.

name: About to Jump
description: A Praying Mantis gauges the distance to another tree before leaping.  To get this shot, I used by ultra-wide angle landscape lens and positioned the camera about 2 inches away from the subject.

name: Swan Portrait
description: A swan preens its feathers in the shallows of a lake in central Texas.

name: Mantis Pastel
description: A soft portrait of a Praying Mantis in tall grass in western Oregon.  To get this image, I held the camera flat on the ground so that grass would be partly blocking the subject from the lens.

name: Spider in Marsh Grass
description: A small spider and golden grass in a pond in western oregon.

name: Watchful Mantis
description: A Praying Mantis eyes me from its formidable home in central Arizona.

name: Oregon Fall
description: Brice Creek flows through a leaf-covered landscape in western Oregon.

name: Lone Fir
description: A huge Douglas Fir stands as the sole reminder of a clear-cut forest.  They often leave one tree ever few hundred feet or so in northwest clearcuts, either for wildlife or to help re-seed the area.  This image was the Winner of the One Earth Award category of the BBC Wildlife Photographer of the Year.

name: Wary Basilisk
description: A large Basilisk lizard keeps an eye on me through the underbrush in Corcovado National Park.

name: Hanging On
description: A Green Anole lizard ends up in a funny pose while trying to escape the photographer.

name: Anole Display
description: A small anole lizard warns another to keep its distance on the Osa Peninsula of Costa Rica.  It was only after I got the slides back and was examining this one that I noticed the tiny hopper in the crook of the lizard's tail.

name: Moon Over Tidal Pool
description: A full moon at sunrise over sea foam swirling in a tidal pool on the Oregon coast.

name: Northern Moon
description: A triple exposure of the moon, the western horizon, and the northern sky.  For the first exposure I used my longest telephoto lens and took a simple shot of the moon in the center of the frame, then without forwarding the film I rotated the camera and took a 10 minute shot of the last glow on the western horizon, and finally I turned the camera to the dark northern sky and left the shutter open until dawn.

name: Resisting the Current
description: Fall leaves hold to the rock riverbed, resisting the swift current.  When I took this photograph, my feet were inches from a steep drop off behind me and the flowing water was rattling my legs and those of my tripod.

name: Maple Leaf in Stream
description: The rushing water of a stream pins a maple leaf to limestone in central Texas.

name: Jupiter and Venus
description: Two planets streak together in a 45 minute exposure illuminated by the rising moon.  I'd spent so much time in White Sands I was pretty familiar with the movement of the stars and planets, and knew that Venus and Jupiter set at an angle instead of straight down.  My hope was that they would look like meteors streaking towards Earth, and I think it worked out well.

name: Cedar Pastel
description: Frozen water drops cling to this Western Red Cedar branch in western Oregon.  Color like this is something I miss from my film days, it just doesn't seem as good with digital.

name: Polaris and Ponderosa
description: A Ponderosa Pine is framed by stars on a hillside in western Washington.

name: Joshua Tree Night
description: Star trails from an 8 hour exposure in Joshua Tree National Park.

name: Joined
description: A simple portrait of two seeds on a soggy Oregon winter morning.  On such days, which account for about 2/3 of the year here, I have to wear a rain jacket and hip waders to keep dry, and use an umbrella and protective cover for my camera.

name: Dreamy Fall Pond
description: Leaves swirl in the current in a little pond in Western Oregon.  Towards the end of the long exposure, I moved the camera around slightly to add softness to the scene.

name: Skimmer Waves
description: A water skimmer pulses forward and sends out smooth ripples in a pond in western Oregon.

name: Morning Frost
description: A leaf and some reeds are covered in frost after a cold night in western Oregon.

name: Lines and Shadows
description: A lone creosote bush casts it's shadow on white sand.  It's interesting being in a place where the shadows of things make better photographic subjects than the things themselves.

name: Side Orb Weaver
description: A side view of an Orb Weaver spider in a field in western Oregon.

name: Patterns
description: The sun filters through a small bush in White Sands National Monument.

name: Needles in Stream
description: Ice clings to pine needles in a creek in the Gila Wilderness.

name: Long Shadow
description: Short bushes cast long shadows on the dunes in White Sands National Monument.

name: Haystack Moonset
description: The full moon sets over Haystack Rock on the Oregon coast.

name: Into the Storm
description: Car tail lights snake toward a lightning storm in West Texas.  I had set up the exposure to catch the lighting, and nearly took it down when I saw the car "ruining" the image. Glad I didn't.

name: Havasu Slot
description: A sandstone wall and blue sky reflected in a creek in Havasu Canyon.

name: Tree Frog on Fern
description: A Green Tree Frog about to jump from a fern in the understory of a forest in Western Oregon.

name: Grass Reflection
description: A long grass stem mirrored in the water of a flooded forest.

name: Wind Tossed Aspens
description: One of my favorite things to see is Aspen leaves quaking in the wind.  Here, a tall Aspen stand is blown around by strong winds in the Gila Wilderness.

name: Grand Canyon Star Trails
description: Star trails over rocky cliffs in the Grand Canyon.  It was difficult positioning the North Star at the rock pinnacle where I wanted it in the pitch dark, but after a while my eyes adjusted enough to compose the shot.

name: Entwined
description: Two identical blades of frost-covered grass entwined together into a familiar shape.  To get the detail I wanted, I took four separate vertical photographs and spliced them together.

name: Glass Frog Portrait
description: A nearly translucent tree frog holds perfectly still for a 30 second exposure in the Ecuadorian Andes.

name: Gray Frog
description: An unusual view over the shoulder of a tree frog near the bottom of the Grand Canyon.

name: Costa Rica Tree Frog
description: In the dark rainforest understory a 30 second exposure was necessary to illuminate this tiny tree frog.  After jumping from one spot to another it would gather it's body together in a little wiggle and all the lines from its legs and arms would disappear, leaving just a green oval.

name: Lantern
description: A tiny, translucent seed head framed against the sky.

name: Framed Seedling
description: A tiny desert plant frames another in central Arizona.  To get a low enough angle for the shot, I dug a small hole in the sand and laid my camera in it, so the lens was level with the ground.

name: Fall Web
description: An orb weaver waits for prey in front of changing foliage in western Oregon.

name: Rising Above the Flood
description: A spider floats on the rainforest floor in Tambopata Preserve.  It was a difficult photo to get because every movement I made disturbed the water, and my back was covered in biting mosquitos.

name: Thawing Out
description: Warming up after a frigid night in White Sands.  The long winter nights can be difficult to go through, but an advantage is that one can get plenty of sleep and still be awake for the first faint glow of sunrise.

name: Seeking Warmth
description: The Arizona Trail runs 800 miles from Mexico to Utah, and one winter I decided to hike a 300 mile section of it from Tucson to north of Phoenix.  It was incredibly lonely as solo winter hiking often is, but evening fires were always helpful.

name: Wintry Fir Forest
description: A wintry panorama of a Douglas Fir stand on the trail leading to Moon Falls in western Oregon.

name: Wing Bokeh
description: An early morning portrait of a dragonfly with dew-soaked wings, clinging to a long grass head.

name: Reaching Out
description: A Praying Mantis reaches out and reveals one of the black spots on the inside of the base of each arm.  It must be for mating purposes because it certainly doesn't help with camouflage.

name: Yanayacu Sunrise
description: For almost all of the 30 or so days I spent in the cloud forest in easter Ecuador, the view from my bunk was the same; a gray curtain.  On this morning, the fog lifted long enough for me to actually see the surrounding forest.

name: First Light
description: The first rays of sunlight reach a waiting dragonfly.

name: Buried
description: Dried flowers under freshly fallen snow in northern New Mexico.

name: Peruvian Walking Stick
description: A walking stick rests on a leaf in the Peruvian Amazon.

name: Suspended
description: A tiny droplet hangs in midair over the water's surface.  It took a lot of shooting while droplets rolled down the leaf into the water before I was able to catch the right moment.

name: Cold In Motion
description: Freezing water rushing through a winter landscape in Oregon's Umpqua National Forest.  Though the hip waders I was wearing kept me from getting wet, after just a minute or two of being waist deep in this water I was beginning to lose feeling in my legs and made a hasty retreat to shore.

name: Deer Creek
description: The waters of Deer Creek rush through this slot canyon before plunging over 100 feet into the Colorado River.  This was one of many side canyon hikes I went on during a 3-week, 250 mile rafting trip of the Grand Canyon, but it was definitely one of the most memorable.

name: Costa Rica Waterfall
description: Two high school friends and I spent a few weeks in Costa Rica during our senior year, and one day we took a hike up a creek to this lovely little waterfall.

name: Damselfly Sun
description: A small damselfly in tall grass, silhouetted against a morning sun filtering through a large oak tree.

name: White Sands Sunrise
description: The curve of a dune at sunrise, its white sand turned golden orange by the early morning light.

name: A Wary Eye
description: A Green Anole clings to a Mexican Juniper in Central Texas, eyeing me warily.  To get this view I had my camera body flush against the tree trunk, pointed straight down.

name: Turbulence
description: Water rushes out of a narrow chute on the Row River in western Oregon.

name: The First Faint Glow
description: The winter nights I spent out in White Sands National Monument were lonely and cold, especially in the evenings when it would get dark at 4 PM and I couldn't get to sleep until 9 or so.  A nice small campfire took some of the chill off the ten degree mornings, and i've always found that they help almost as much with the loneliness.

name: Close to the Sun
description: A young dragonfly soaked up warmth from the rising sun.

name: Leaves Over Snow
description: Cottonwood leaves cling to a branch over a snow covered landscape, long after the arrival of winter.

name: Dragonfly Wave
description: A dragonfly appears to wave in the course of removing the night's dew from its eyes.

name: Coastal Cave
description: The waves thundering through this 200 foot long tunnel on the Oregon Coast were 6 to 10 feet high, so getting a photograph of the scene without getting soaked wasn't easy.  This image was taken just after a wave slammed into the rocks and was receding.

name: Safety in Numbers
description: A carpet of caterpillars on a tree in southern Costa Rica.  I'd been sleeping in the same spot for days before I noticed them, just a few feet from my tent.

name: Stars and Planes
description: A Joshua Tree stands under a mass of lines made by stars and planes moving across the sky.  Planes are ubiquitous now and can seem impossible to keep out of a night shot, especially if you're in the flight path to LAX.

name: Hidden, Sort of
description: A Praying mantis hides poorly under a leaf in western Ecuador.

name: Tree Frog Silhouette
description: The outline of a large tree frog on an elephant ear leaf in western Ecuador.  Called logger frogs by the locals, their nighttime calls sounded for all the world like someone swinging an axe against a hollow log.

name: Brice Creek Falls
description: Fall leaves lay near a double waterfall off the Brice Creek Trail in western Oregon.

name: Twilight Silhouette
description: A large spider silhouetted against the colorful light filtering in through the forest in Corcovado National Park.

name: A Moment of Rest
description: A head-on portrait of a butterfly in Tambopata National Preserve, highlighted by an area of sunlit forest floor.

name: Yucca Moonrise
description: A yucca plant and the rising full moon in White Sands National Park.

name: A Light in the Darkness
description: One of the last leaves of fall, stubbornly clinging to a dormant branch.  In the near darkness, a 30 second exposure was necessary.

name: Oneonta Falls
description: Steep, moss-covered canyon walls surround Oneonta Falls along the Columbia River in Oregon.  It's not easy wading the 1/4 mile or so up this swift-moving river to see the falls, but it's well worth it.

name: Mother Scorpion
description: Baby scorpions ride on their mothers back for the first few weeks of life.

name: Yucca Tangle
description: A close-up view of the tangled fibers and blades of a Yucca in Big Bend National Park.

name: Desert Shadow
description: On my way to Big Bend National Park in west Texas I looked out my car window and saw these beautiful wispy clouds and the small hill in covered in shadow, and quickly jumped out to capture the scene.  But as the sun was low in the sky and directly behind me, I couldn't get my shadow out of the frame, and ended up just deciding to incorporate it into the composition.

name: Wary Anole
description: An Anole lizard eyes me warily from between palm fronds in the Peruvian Amazon.

name: Joshua Tree Sunset
description: Huge piled of boulders dot the strange landscape of Joshua Tree National Park in southern California, left behind as the ground around them erodes away.  There's no better place to watch the sun set over the vast plain, and I took a self portrait on the highest rock, as I was being buffeted by strong winds.

name: Stream of Clouds
description: The entire time I spent in the Alvord Basin, there was a stream of clouds emerging from a group of distant mountains and moving across the sky.  Here they are framed above a golden grass prairie.

name: Alvord Desert Sunset
description: Depending on the time of year, the Alvord Lakebed in Eastern Oregon is dry and cracked, muddy, or underwater.  When I arrived in January it was muddy but the deep cracks were still visible, so I used one to frame a chaotic sunset.

name: Desert Thunderhead
description: The Alvord Desert is a huge, often dry lakebed in far-eastern Oregon.  Small rivers snake down out of the surrounding mountains and disappear quickly into the muddy sand.  By kneeling close to the ground and using an ultra-wide angle lens, I was able to exaggerate the size of this tiny stream under a massive thunderhead.

name: Branch Abstract
description: This long, thin branch was growing in the dark understory of old growth on the Umpqua National Forest.  I framed it against the tall trees and sky, and the high contract between the two washed all color from the scene.

name: Apocalypse
description: The plume roles skyward as the fire rushes away from me on the Hastings Fire outside of Fairbanks, Alaska.

name: Black Smoke
description: Dark smoke from torching trees blocks the sun on a burnout on the Hastings Fire in Alaska. Smoke color is a good indicator of how a fire is progressing and what fuels it's consuming.  White smoke generally means it's consuming light fuels like leaves or grass, while black smoke is from heavy logs burning or tree torching out.

name: Yellow
description: A tiger swallowtail lands on me on a fire in southern California.

name: Wall of Fire
description: Tongues of fire jump through the air from the tops of Black Spruce trees in Alaska.

name: Old Growth Underburn
description: Fire moves along the ground through an old growth stand on the Umpqua National Forest in western Oregon.

name: Gila Peak
description: One day on the Miller Fire we hiked to the highest prominence around to watch for smoke popping up anywhere, and I took a self-portrait.

name: Retardant Drop
description: An air tanker drops a load of retardant on the Brown Road Fire in northern Oregon.

name: Watching For Spots
description: If I could fight fire only at night, I think I would.  A burning landscape at night is one of the most beautiful things i've ever seen, and I think I remember every time I was lucky enough to witness it.  Here a Wolf Creek Hotshot watches the grassy field for falling embers.

name: Ponderosas at Night
description: Our backburn lights up a Ponderosa forest on the Miller Fire in the Gila Wilderness.

name: Socked In
description: After just a few hours on the Hastings Fire, the fire plume laid down and an inversion set it, and we didn't breathe clear air for almost a week.  I remember laying down to sleep and hearing people hacking in their sleeping bags.  Here, 3 dozers move up the line in the dense smoke.

name: Heads Up
description: A helicopter drops its load of water on the Brown Road Fire in northern Oregon.

name: Falling a Fatty
description: One of the biggest trees I cut on fire in 2011.  We rarely cut live trees because fire doesn't climb up them like it climbs dead snags, but this particular one was broken about 60 feet up and the bowl had caught an ember and was throwing sparks day and night.  It took awhile to find it in the dense forest, but finally we did and I took it down.

name: Hitchhiker
description: Halvey picks up a hitchhiker in the course of gridding a grass fire in northern Oregon.

name: Alaska Dozer
description: A massive plume rises behind a bulldozer on the Hastings Fire in Alaska in 2011.

name: Napping
description: Quinn and Mac having a nap on the Hastings Fire.

name: Sun Through Trees
description: The sun illuminates a smoke-filled forest in western Oregon.

name: A Short Break
description: Halvey basks in the glow of a short break while cutting line on an Oregon fire.

name: A Hot Spot
description: My saw partner snapped a photo of me cutting through a burning log on an Oregon fire.  I remember having to tilt my head because the heat was starting to burn my cheek.

name: Coming In To Drop
description: A huge airtanker flies over us before dropping thousands of gallons of fire retardant on the Wildcat Fire in New Mexico.

name: Alaska Lake
description: Clouds drift over a small lake near Fairbanks, Alaska.  I was on pump duty when I took this photo, and spent all day laying next to this lake.  It was one of those times when I couldn't believe I was being paid to do what I was doing.

name: Fallen Giant
description: Halvey sits on the holding wood of a massive tree taken down on a fire in western Oregon.  We counted the rings and got 580.

name: In the Oven
description: Someone took a photo of me cutting a burning snag on the Hastings Fire in 2011.  The ground was too hot to stand on, so before I went in I cut some rounds off a nearby tree and threw them out there like stepping stones.  I could barely breath while cutting the tree, but eventually I got it down.

name: Hummingbird Egg
description: This tiny hummingbird egg was no bigger than a pea.

name: In Need of a Shower
description: My saw partner after almost 2 weeks without a shower.

name: Taking Stock
description: Eric Miller (I can tell by the stance) surveys the strange landscape of northeastern Oregon on the Brown Road Fire.

name: Falling a Snag
description: My saw partner finishes a humboldt cut on a large pine snag in the Gila Wilderness.

name: Scarred Aspen
description: An Aspen trunk scarred by a black bear on a fire in Utah.

name: Around the Campfire
description: We spent about ten days spiked out on the Miller Fire in the Gila Wilderness in 2011.  Here we're sitting around a campfire telling tall tales after a long day of cutting line in 4% relative humidity.

name: Crane Your Neck
description: To see the top of this plume, I had to look basically straight up over my head.

name: Berry Pistols
description: Two member of the Rogue River Hotshots fire igniting rounds into the forest to get some depth on a burnout.

name: Moth Eye Spots
description: A beautiful moth in my hand on a fire in New Mexico.

name: Reunited
description: My old crew and my new crew run into each other on a remote fire in southern New Mexico.  It's rare for Hotshot crews to work together directly, usually each takes its own section and they leapfrog each other, but the nature of this grass fire made that impossible.  So the crews basically fused together and became a 40-man firefighting machine for a few hours.  In this photo, we're watching as a pulse of strong wind carries the fire up a hillside in seconds.

name: Fly-over
description: An airtanker flies over my head on the Hastings Fire outside of Fairbanks, Alaska in 2011.

name: Havin' a Stogie
description: As if breathing wildfire smoke isn't enough, Quinn lights up a stogie during a mop-up day on the Hastings Fire in Alaska.

name: Morning Briefing
description: Sunbeams break through the smoke during one of our morning briefings on the Whiskey Complex in 2008 in Northern California.

name: Defying Gravity
description: No, I'm not really defying gravity.  In cutting the top off this stump as we usually do after falling a tree, I accidentally left a small plug of wood attached, so when I went to push it off it caught.  Amazingly, that little plug was strong enough to hold my weight.

name: The Morning After
description: Natalee and Miller warm up after a night of chasing down a running grass fire.  It was exhausting, but I love watching the sunrise from the first faint glow.

name: Leading The Way
description: The assistant superintendent of Wolf Creek, Jason Amis, leads us on a hike out of the 60 foot wide saw cut we made through the thick black spruce.  I heard this contingency line never got used, but I'm sure the moose will love it.

name: Dismembered
description: On a remote fire in Montana I came across this coyote paw laying on the ground.

name: Plume Behind Buggies
description: The plume from the Elkhorn 2 fire arches over the Carson Hotshots buggies in Nevada in 2008.

name: Engulfed
description: This old Juniper tree had a little bit of fire at it's base, but after I got it on the ground it took less than a minute for it to become fully engulfed in flames.

name: Utah Sunset
description: The setting sun lights up mountains in Utah.

name: Elk Sheds
description: Halvey adds about 30 pounds to his packweight with three elk sheds.

name: Torching
description: Evergreen tree needles contain flammable oils that cause the trees to go up like they've been doused in gasoline.  In this photo you can see those burning embers from a tree shooting up into the night sky.

name: Butterfly Self-Portrait
description: I'm fortunate enough to spend so much time in the woods that usually several times per year a tiger swallowtail butterfly lands on me.

name: Ancient Burned Tree
description: A thunderhead builds over a long-ago burned tree in central New Mexico.

name: Mopping Up
description: My saw partner pounds out an ember the morning after a night shift.

name: Relaxing in the Sun
description: I joined our lookout and relaxed for a little while one day on a fire in Wyoming.  I have two tools because the swamper carries one for the sawyer on mop-up days.
